&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for the post of Clerk/Typist within the Haematology Department at Morriston Hospital, based in Swansea Bay University Health Board. &lt;br /&gt;The successful individual will need to be a hardworking, team player with the ability to prioritise work and possess good verbal and written communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicants should possess a recognised word processing/typing qualification to RSA III, NVQ III Level or demonstrable experience at this level with experience of working in a busy administrative / office environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The applicant will be required to have a flexible approach towards the needs of the service and be able to travel between sites in a timely manner when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
